{
  "texts": [
    "Chinese private university students often face challenges in foreign language proficiency (Lee et al., 2022).",
    "However, they compensate for their expression deficiencies by actively working towards acquiring a competent level of English-speaking skills (Sun, 2022).",
    "Speaking proficiency involves not only the ability to choose and arrange sounds in a language (Zhou, 2021), but also understanding how these sounds function in English, and what it means to effectively communicate in English-speaking contexts.",
    "Englishspeaking proficiency plays a crucial role in helping college students produce accurate and natural sounds (Meade, 2020).",
    "BL settings, as discussed by Abugohar et al. (2019), integrate traditional face-to-face instruction with online and digital learning pedagogy in the context of listening and speaking."
  ]
}